I89. Safety standards

I11(a) The Secretary shall prescribe regulations which require that each vessel to which this chapter applies shall be equipped with_

I12(1) readily accessible fire extinguishers capable of promptly and effectively extinguishing a flammable or combustible liquid fuel fire;

I12(2) at least one readily accessible life preserver or other lifesaving device for each individual on board;

I12(3) an efficient flame arrestor, backfire trap, or other similar device on the carburetors of each inboard engine which uses gasoline as fuel;

I12(4) the means to properly and efficiently ventilate enclosed spaces, including engine and fuel tank compartments, so as to remove explosive or flammable gases;

I12(5) visual distress signals;

I12(6) other equipment required to minimize the risk of injury to the crew during vessel operations, if the Secretary determines that a risk of serious injury exists that can be eliminated or mitigated by that equipment; and

I12(7) a placard as required by regulations prescribed under section 10603(b) of this title.

