I89. Bases for suspension or revocation

I11A license, certificate of registry, or merchant mariner's document issued by the Secretary may be suspended or revoked if the holder_

I12(1) when acting under the authority of that license, certificate, or document_

I13(A) has violated or fails to comply with this subtitle, a regulation prescribed under this subtitle, or any other law or regulation intended to promote marine safety or to protect navigable waters; or

I13(B) has committed an act of misconduct or negligence;

Q04

I12(2) is convicted of an offense that would prevent the issuance or renewal of a license, certificate of registry, or merchant mariner's document;

I12(3) within the 3-year period preceding the initiation of the suspension or revocation proceeding is convicted of an offense described in section 30304(a)(3)(A) or (B) of title 49;

