I89. Purposes

I11The purposes of this part are to_

I12(1) establish a nondiscriminatory regulatory process for the common carriage of goods by water in the foreign commerce of the United States with a minimum of government intervention and regulatory costs;

I12(2) provide an efficient and economic transportation system in the ocean commerce of the United States that is, insofar as possible, in harmony with, and responsive to, international shipping practices;

I12(3) encourage the development of an economically sound and efficient liner fleet of vessels of the United States capable of meeting national security needs; and

I12(4) promote the growth and development of United States exports through competitive and efficient ocean transportation and by placing a greater reliance on the marketplace.

