I12(3) T4Assessment agreementK._The term ``assessment agreement'' means an agreement, whether part of a collective bargaining agreement or negotiated separately, to the extent the agreement provides for the funding of collectively bargained fringe-benefit obligations on other than a uniform worker-hour basis, regardless of the cargo handled or type of vessel or equipment used.

I12(4) T4Bulk cargoK._The term ``bulk cargo'' means cargo that is loaded and carried in bulk without mark or count.

I12(5) T4Chemical parcel-tankerK._The term ``chemical parcel-tanker'' means a vessel that has_

I13(A) a cargo-carrying capability consisting of individual cargo tanks for bulk chemicals that_

I14(i) are a permanent part of the vessel; and

I14(ii) have segregation capability with piping systems to permit simultaneous carriage of several bulk chemical cargoes with minimum risk of cross-contamination; and

Q04

I13(B) a valid certificate of fitness under the International Maritime Organization Code for the Construction and Equipment of Ships Carrying Dangerous Chemicals in Bulk.

Q04

I12(6) T4Common carrierK._The term ``common carrier''_

I13(A) means a person that_

I14(i) holds itself out to the general public to provide transportation by water of passengers or cargo between the United States and a foreign country for compensation;

I14(ii) assumes responsibility for the transportation from the port or point of receipt to the port or point of destination; and

I14(iii) uses, for all or part of that transportation, a vessel operating on the high seas or the Great Lakes between a port in the United States and a port in a foreign country; but

Q04

I13(B) does not include a carrier engaged in ocean transportation by ferry boat, ocean tramp, or chemical parcel-tanker, or by vessel when primarily engaged in the carriage of perishable agricultural commodities_

I14(i) if the carrier and the owner of those commodities are wholly-owned, directly or indirectly, by a person primarily engaged in the marketing and distribution of those commodities; and

I14(ii) only with respect to the carriage of those commodities.

Q04

I12(7) T4ConferenceK._The term ``conference''_

I13(A) means an association of ocean common carriers permitted, pursuant to an approved or effective agreement, to engage in concerted activity and to use a common tariff; but

I13(B) does not include a joint service, consortium, pooling, sailing, or transshipment agreement.

Q04

I12(8) T4Controlled carrierK._The term ``controlled carrier'' means an ocean common carrier that is, or whose operating assets are, directly or indirectly, owned or controlled by a government, with ownership or control by a government being deemed to exist for a carrier if_

I13(A) a majority of the interest in the carrier is owned or controlled in any manner by that government, an agency of that government, or a public or private person controlled by that government; or

I13(B) that government has the right to appoint or disapprove the appointment of a majority of the directors, the chief operating officer, or the chief executive officer of the carrier.

Q04

I12(9) T4Deferred rebateK._The term ``deferred rebate'' means a return by a common carrier of any freight money to a shipper, where the return is_

I13(A) consideration for the shipper giving all or any portion of its shipments to that or any other common carrier over a fixed period of time;

I13(B) deferred beyond the completion of the service for which it was paid; and

I13(C) made only if the shipper has agreed to make a further shipment with that or any other common carrier.

Q04

I12(10) T4Forest productsK._The term ``forest products'' includes lumber in bundles, rough timber, ties, poles, piling, laminated beams, bundled siding, bundled plywood, bundled core stock or veneers, bundled particle or fiber boards, bundled hardwood, wood pulp in rolls, wood pulp in unitized bales, and paper and paper board in rolls or in pallet or skid-sized sheets.

I12(11) T4Inland divisionK._The term ``inland division'' means the amount paid by a common carrier to an inland carrier for the inland portion of through transportation offered to the public by the common carrier.

I12(12) T4Inland portionK._The term ``inland portion'' means the charge to the public by a common carrier for the non-ocean portion of through transportation.

I12(13) T4Loyalty contractK._The term ``loyalty contract'' means a contract with an ocean common carrier or agreement providing for_

I13(A) a shipper to obtain lower rates by committing all or a fixed portion of its cargo to that carrier or agreement; and

I13(B) a deferred rebate arrangement.

Q04

I12(14) T4Marine terminal operatorK._The term ``marine terminal operator'' means a person engaged in the United States in the business of providing wharfage, dock, warehouse, or other terminal facilities in connection with a common carrier, or in connection with a common carrier and a water carrier subject to subchapter II of chapter 135 of title 49.

I12(15) T4Maritime labor agreementK._The term ``maritime labor agreement''_

I13(A) means_

I14(i) a collective bargaining agreement between an employer subject to this part, or a group of such employers, and a labor organization representing employees in the maritime or stevedoring industry;

I14(ii) an agreement preparatory to such a collective bargaining agreement among members of a multi-employer bargaining group; or

I14(iii) an agreement specifically implementing provisions of such a collective bargaining agreement or providing for the formation, financing, or administration of a multi-employer bargaining group; but

Q04

I13(B) does not include an assessment agreement.

Q04

I12(16) T4Non-vessel-operating common carrierK._The term ``non-vessel-operating common carrier'' means a common carrier that_

I13(A) does not operate the vessels by which the ocean transportation is provided; and

I13(B) is a shipper in its relationship with an ocean common carrier.

Q04

I12(17) T4Ocean common carrierK._The term ``ocean common carrier'' means a vessel-operating common carrier.

I12(18) T4Ocean freight forwarderK._The term ``ocean freight forwarder'' means a person that_

I13(A) in the United States, dispatches shipments from the United States via a common carrier and books or otherwise arranges space for those shipments on behalf of shippers; and

I13(B) processes the documentation or performs related activities incident to those shipments.

Q04

I12(19) T4Ocean transportation intermediaryK._The term ``ocean transportation intermediary'' means an ocean freight forwarder or a non-vessel-operating common carrier.

I12(20) T4Service contractK._The term ``service contract'' means a written contract, other than a bill of lading or receipt, between one or more shippers, on the one hand, and an individual ocean common carrier or an agreement between or among ocean common carriers, on the other, in which_

I13(A) the shipper or shippers commit to providing a certain volume or portion of cargo over a fixed time period; and

I13(B) the ocean common carrier or the agreement commits to a certain rate or rate schedule and a defined service level, such as assured space, transit time, port rotation, or similar service features.

Q04

I12(21) T4ShipmentK._The term ``shipment'' means all of the cargo carried under the terms of a single bill of lading.

I12(22) T4ShipperK._The term ``shipper'' means_

I13(A) a cargo owner;

I13(B) the person for whose account the ocean transportation of cargo is provided;

I13(C) the person to whom delivery is to be made;

I13(D) a shippers' association; or

I13(E) a non-vessel-operating common carrier that accepts responsibility for payment of all charges applicable under the tariff or service contract.

Q04

I12(23) T4Shippers' associationK._The term ``shippers' association'' means a group of shippers that consolidates or distributes freight on a nonprofit basis for the members of the group to obtain carload, truckload, or other volume rates or service contracts.

I12(24) T4Through rateK._The term ``through rate'' means the single amount charged by a common carrier in connection with through transportation.

I12(25) T4Through transportationK._The term ``through transportation'' means continuous transportation between origin and destination for which a through rate is assessed and which is offered or performed by one or more carriers, at least one of which is a common carrier, between a United States port or point and a foreign port or point.

