I89. Application

I11(a) T4Ocean Common Carrier AgreementsK._This part applies to an agreement between or among ocean common carriers to_

I12(1) discuss, fix, or regulate transportation rates, including through rates, cargo space accommodations, and other conditions of service;

I12(2) pool or apportion traffic, revenues, earnings, or losses;

I12(3) allot ports or regulate the number and character of voyages between ports;

I12(4) regulate the volume or character of cargo or passenger traffic to be carried;

I12(5) engage in an exclusive, preferential, or cooperative working arrangement between themselves or with a marine terminal operator;

I12(6) control, regulate, or prevent competition in international ocean transportation; or

I12(7) discuss and agree on any matter related to a service contract.

Q04

I11(b) T4Marine Terminal Operator AgreementsK._This part applies to an agreement between or among marine terminal operators, or between or among one or more marine terminal operators and one or more ocean common carriers, to_

I12(1) discuss, fix, or regulate rates or other conditions of service; or

I12(2) engage in exclusive, preferential, or cooperative working arrangements, to the extent the agreement involves ocean transportation in the foreign commerce of the United States.

Q04

I11(c) T4AcquisitionsK._This part does not apply to an acquisition by any person, directly or indirectly, of any voting security or assets of any other person.

I11(d) T4Maritime Labor AgreementsK._This part does not apply to a maritime labor agreement. However, this subsection does not exempt from this part any rate, charge, regulation, or practice of a common carrier that is required to be set forth in a tariff or is an essential term of a service contract, whether or not the rate, charge, regulation, or practice arises out of, or is otherwise related to, a maritime labor agreement.

I11(e) T4Assessment AgreementsK._This part (except sections 40305 and 40307(a)) does not apply to an assessment agreement.

