I11In this chapter:

I12(1) T4Bulk cargoK._The term ``bulk cargo'' means cargo that is loaded and carried in bulk without mark or count.

I12(2) T4ContractorK._The term ``contractor'' means an owner or operator of a vessel that enters into an operating agreement for the vessel with the Secretary under section 53103.

I12(3) T4FleetK._The term ``Fleet'' means the Maritime Security Fleet established under section 53102(a).

I12(4) T4Foreign commerceK._The term ``foreign commerce'' means_

I13(A) commerce or trade between the United States, its territories or possessions, or the District of Columbia, and a foreign country; and

I13(B) commerce or trade between foreign countries.

Q04

I12(5) LASH T4vesselK._The term ``LASH vessel'' means a lighter aboard ship vessel.

I12(6) T4Participating fleet vesselK._The term ``participating fleet vessel'' means any vessel that_

I13(A) on October 1, 2005_

I14(i) meets the requirements of paragraph (1), (2), (3), or (4) of section 53102(c); and

I14(ii) is less than 25 years of age, or less than 30 years of age in the case of a LASH vessel; and

Q04

I13(B) on December 31, 2004, is covered by an operating agreement under subtitle B of title VI of the Merchant Marine Act, 1936 (46 U.S.C. App. 1187 et seq.).\1\N

I28N\1\ÿ1ASee References in Text note below.

