I80ÿ1A53701

I89. Definitions

I11In this chapter:

I12(1) T4Actual costK._The term ``actual cost'' means the sum of_

I13(A) all amounts paid by or for the account of the obligor as of the date on which a determination is made under section 53715(d)(1) of this title; and

I13(B) all amounts that the Secretary or Administrator reasonably estimates the obligor will become obligated to pay from time to time thereafter, for the construction, reconstruction, or reconditioning of the vessel, including guarantee fees that will become payable under section 53714 of this title in connection with all obligations issued for construction, reconstruction, or reconditioning of the vessel or equipment to be delivered, and all obligations issued for the delivered vessel or equipment.

Q04

I12(2) T4AdministratorK._The term ``Administrator'' means the Administrator of the Maritime Administration.

I12(3) T4Construction, reconstruction, and reconditioningK._The terms ``construction'', ``reconstruction'', and ``reconditioning'' include designing, inspecting, outfitting, and equipping.

I12(4) T4Depreciated actual costK._The term ``depreciated actual cost'' of a vessel means_

I13(A) if the vessel was not reconstructed or reconditioned, the actual cost of the vessel depreciated on a straight line basis over the useful life of the vessel as determined by the Secretary or Administrator, not to exceed 25 years from the date of delivery by the builder; or

I13(B) if the vessel was reconstructed or reconditioned, the sum of_

I14(i) the actual cost of the vessel depreciated on a straight line basis from the date of delivery by the builder to the date of the reconstruction or reconditioning, using the original useful life of the vessel, and from the date of the reconstruction or reconditioning, using a useful life of the vessel determined by the Secretary or Administrator; and

I14(ii) any amount paid or obligated to be paid for the reconstruction or reconditioning, depreciated on a straight line basis using a useful life of the vessel determined by the Secretary or Administrator.

Q04

I12(5) T4Eligible export vesselK._The term ``eligible export vessel'' means a vessel that_

I13(A) is constructed, reconstructed, or reconditioned in the United States for use in world-wide trade; and

I13(B) will, on delivery or redelivery, become or remain documented under the laws of a country other than the United States.

Q04

I12(6) T4Fishery facilityK._

I13(A) T4In generalK._Subject to subparagraph (B), the term ``fishery facility'' means_

I14(i) for operations on land_

I16(I) a structure or appurtenance thereto designed for the unloading and receiving from vessels, the processing, the holding pending processing, the distribution after processing, or the holding pending distribution, of fish from a fishery;

I16(II) the land necessary for the structure or appurtenance; and

I16(III) equipment that is for use with the structure or appurtenance and that is necessary for performing a function referred to in subclause (I);

Q04

I14(ii) for operations not on land, a vessel built in the United States and used for, equipped to be used for, or of a type normally used for, the processing of fish; or

I14(iii) for aquaculture, including operations on land or elsewhere_

I16(I) a structure or appurtenance thereto designed for aquaculture;

I16(II) the land necessary for the structure or appurtenance;

I16(III) equipment that is for use with the structure or appurtenance and that is necessary for performing a function referred to in subclause (I); and

I16(IV) a vessel built in the United States and used for, equipped to be used for, or of a type normally used for, aquaculture.

Q04

I13(B) T4Required ownershipK._Under subparagraph (A), the structure, appurtenance, land, equipment, or vessel must be owned by_

I14(i) an individual who is a citizen of the United States; or

I14(ii) an entity that is a citizen of the United States under section 50501 of this title and that is at least 75 percent owned (as determined under that section) by citizens of the United States.

Q04

I12(7) T4Fishing vesselK._The term ``fishing vessel'' has the meaning given that term in section 3 of the Magnuson-Stevens Fishery Conservation and Management Act (16 U.S.C. 1802), and any reference in this chapter to a vessel designed principally for commercial use in the fishing trade or industry is deemed to be a reference to a fishing vessel.

I12(8) T4MortgageK._The term ``mortgage'' includes_

I13(A) a preferred mortgage as defined in section 31301 of this title; and

I13(B) a mortgage on a vessel that will become a preferred mortgage when filed or recorded under chapter 313 of this title.

Q04

I12(9) T4ObligationK._The term ``obligation'' means an instrument of indebtedness issued for a purpose described in section 53706 of this title, except_

I13(A) an obligation issued by the Secretary or Administrator under section 53723 of this title; and

I13(B) an obligation eligible for investment of funds under section 53715(f) or 53717 of this title.

Q04

I12(10) T4ObligeeK._The term ``obligee'' means the holder of an obligation.

I12(11) T4ObligorK._The term ``obligor'' means a party primarily liable for payment of the principal of or interest on an obligation.

I12(12) T4Ocean thermal energy conversion facility or plantshipK._The term ``ocean thermal energy conversion facility or plantship'' means an at-sea facility or vessel, whether mobile, floating unmoored, moored, or standing on the seabed, that uses temperature differences in ocean water to produce electricity or another form of energy capable of being used directly to perform work, and includes_

I13(A) equipment installed on the facility or vessel to use the electricity or other form of energy to produce, process, refine, or manufacture a product;

I13(B) a cable or pipeline used to deliver the electricity, freshwater, or product to shore; and

I13(C) other associated equipment and appurtenances of the facility or vessel to the extent they are located seaward of the high water mark.

Q04

I12(13) T4SecretaryK._The term ``Secretary'' means the Secretary of Commerce with respect to fishing vessels and fishery facilities.

I12(14) T4VesselK._The term ``vessel'' means any type of vessel, whether in existence or under construction, including_

I13(A) a cargo vessel;

I13(B) a passenger vessel;

I13(C) a combination cargo and passenger vessel;

I13(D) a tanker;

I13(E) a tug or towboat;

I13(F) a barge;

I13(G) a dredge;

I13(H) a floating drydock with a capacity of at least 35,000 lifting tons and a beam of at least 125 feet between the wing walls;

I13(I) an oceanographic research vessel;

I13(J) an instruction vessel;

I13(K) a pollution treatment, abatement, or control vessel;

I13(L) a fishing vessel whose ownership meets the citizenship requirements under section 50501 of this title for documenting vessels to operate in the coastwise trade; and

I13(M) an ocean thermal energy conversion facility or plantship that is or will be documented under the laws of the United States.

