I80ÿ1A53714

I89. Guarantee fees

I11(a) T4RegulationsK._Subject to this section, the Secretary or Administrator shall prescribe regulations to assess a fee for guaranteeing an obligation under this chapter.

I11(b) T4Computation of FeeK._

I12(1) T4In generalK._The amount of the fee for a guarantee under this chapter shall be equal to the sum of the amounts determined under paragraph (2) for the years in which the guarantee is in effect.

I12(2) T4Present value for each yearK._The amount referred to in paragraph (1) for a year in which the guarantee is in effect is the present value of the amount calculated under paragraph (3). To determine the present value, the Secretary or Administrator shall apply a discount rate determined by the Secretary of the Treasury, considering current market yields on outstanding obligations of the United States Government having periods to maturity comparable to the period to maturity for the guaranteed obligation.

I12(3) T4Calculation of amountK._The amount referred to in paragraph (2) shall be calculated by multiplying_

I13(A) the estimated average unpaid principal amount of the obligation that will be outstanding during the year (excluding the average amount, other than interest, on deposit during the year in an escrow fund under section 53715 of this title); by

I13(B) the fee rate set under paragraph (4).

Q04

I12(4) T4Setting fee ratesK._To set the fee rate referred to in paragraph (3)(B), the Secretary or Administrator shall establish a formula that_

I13(A) takes into account the security provided for the guaranteed obligation; and

I13(B) is a sliding scale based on the creditworthiness of the obligor, using_

I14(i) the lowest allowable rate under paragraph (5) for the most creditworthy obligors; and

I14(ii) the highest allowable rate under paragraph (5) for the least creditworthy obligors.

Q04

I12(5) T4Permissible range of ratesK._The fee rate set under paragraph (4) shall be_

I13(A) for a delivered vessel or equipment, at least 0.5 percent and not more than 1 percent; and

I13(B) for a vessel to be constructed, reconstructed, or reconditioned or equipment to be delivered, at least 0.25 percent and not more than 0.5 percent.

Q04

I11(c) T4When Fee CollectedK._A fee for the guarantee of an obligation under this chapter shall be collected not later than the date on which an amount is first paid on the obligation.

I11(d) T4Financing the FeeK._A fee paid under this section is eligible to be financed under this chapter and shall be included in the actual cost of the obligation guaranteed.

I11(e) T4Not RefundableK._A fee paid under this section is not refundable. However, an obligor shall receive credit for the amount paid for the remaining term of the obligation if the obligation is refinanced and guaranteed under this chapter after the refinancing.

