I89. Assistance for small shipyards and maritime communities

I11(a) T4Establishment of ProgramK._Subject to the availability of appropriations, the Administrator of the Maritime Administration shall execute agreements with shipyards to provide assistance_

I12(1) in the form of grants, loans, and loan guarantees to small shipyards for capital improvements; and

I12(2) for maritime training programs to foster technical skills and operational productivity in communities whose economies are related to or dependent upon the maritime industry.

Q04

I11(b) T4AwardsK._In providing assistance under the program, the Administrator shall_

I12(1) take into account_

I13(A) the economic circumstances and conditions of maritime communities;

I13(B) projects that would be effective in fostering efficiency, competitive operations, and quality ship construction, repair, and reconfiguration; and

I13(C) projects that would be effective in fostering employee skills and enhancing productivity; and

Q04

I12(2) make grants within 120 days after the date of enactment of the appropriations Act for the fiscal year concerned.

Q04

I11(c) T4Use of Funds._

I12(1) T4In generalK._Assistance provided under this section may be used_

I13(A) to make capital and related improvements in small shipyards located in or near maritime communities;

I13(B) to provide training for workers in communities whose economies are related to the maritime industry; and

I13(C) for such other purposes as the Administrator determines to be consistent with and supplemental to such activities.

Q04

I12(2) T4Administrative costsK._Not more than 2 percent of amounts made available to carry out the program may be used for the necessary costs of grant administration.

Q04

I11(d) T4Prohibited UsesK._Grants awarded under this section may not be used to construct buildings or other physical facilities or to acquire land unless such use is specifically approved by the Administrator in support of subsection (c)(1)(C).

I11(e) T4Matching Requirements; Allocation._

