I81SUBCHAPTER II_EXPORT TRANSPORTATION OF AGRICULTURAL COMMODITIES

I80ÿ1A55311

I89. Findings and purposes

I11(a) T4FindingsK._Congress finds that_

I12(1) a productive and healthy agricultural industry and a strong and active United States maritime industry are vitally important to the economic well-being and security of the United States;

I12(2) both industries must compete in international markets increasingly dominated by foreign trade barriers and the subsidization practices of foreign governments; and

I12(3) increased agricultural exports and the use of merchant vessels of the United States contribute positively to the United States balance of trade and generate employment opportunities in the United States.

Q04

I11(b) T4PurposesK._The purposes of this subchapter are to_

I12(1) enable the Secretary of Agriculture to plan export programs effectively, by clarifying the ocean transportation requirements applicable to those programs;

I12(2) take immediate and positive steps to promote the growth of the cargo-carrying capacity of the United States merchant marine;

I12(3) expand international trade in United States agricultural commodities and products and develop, maintain, and expand markets for United States agricultural exports;

I12(4) improve the efficiency of administration of both the commodity purchasing and selling activities and the ocean transportation activities associated with export programs sponsored by the Secretary;

I12(5) stimulate and promote the agricultural and maritime industries of the United States and encourage cooperative efforts by both industries to address their common problems; and

I12(6) provide for the appropriate disposition of these findings and purposes.

I53(Pub. L. 109ÿ09304, ÿ1A8(c), Oct. 6, 2006, 120 Stat. 1643.)

