I89. Short sea transportation program

I11(a) T4EstablishmentK._The Secretary of Transportation shall establish a short sea transportation program and designate short sea transportation projects to be conducted under the program to mitigate landside congestion or to promote short sea transportation.

I11(b) T4Program ElementsK._The program shall encourage the use of short sea transportation through the development and expansion of_

I12(1) documented vessels;

I12(2) shipper utilization;

I12(3) port and landside infrastructure; and

I12(4) marine transportation strategies by State and local governments.

Q04

I11(c) T4Short Sea Transportation RoutesK._The Secretary shall designate short sea transportation routes as extensions of the surface transportation system to focus public and private efforts to use the waterways to relieve landside congestion along coastal corridors or to promote short sea transportation. The Secretary may collect and disseminate data for the designation and delineation of short sea transportation routes.

I11(d) T4Project DesignationK._The Secretary may designate a project to be a short sea transportation project if the Secretary determines that the project uses documented vessels and_

I12(1) mitigates landside congestion; or

I12(2) promotes short sea transportation.

Q04

I11(e) T4Elements of ProgramK._For a short sea transportation project designated under this section, the Secretary may_

I12(1) promote the development of short sea transportation services;

I12(2) coordinate, with ports, State departments of transportation, localities, other public agencies, and the private sector and on the development of landside facilities and infrastructure to support short sea transportation services; and

I12(3) develop performance measures for the short sea transportation program.

Q04

I11(f) T4Multistate, State and Regional Transportation PlanningK._The Secretary, in consultation with Federal entities and State and local governments, may develop strategies to encourage the use of short sea transportation for transportation of passengers and cargo. The Secretary may_

I12(1) assess the extent to which States and local governments include short sea transportation and other marine transportation solutions in their transportation planning;

I12(2) encourage State departments of transportation to develop strategies, where appropriate, to incorporate short sea transportation, ferries, and other marine transportation solutions for regional and interstate transport of freight and passengers in their transportation planning; and

I12(3) encourage groups of States and multi-State transportation entities to determine how short sea transportation can address congestion, bottlenecks, and other interstate transportation challenges.

Q04

I11(g) T4Grants._

I12(1) T4In generalK._The Secretary shall establish and implement a short sea transportation grant program to implement projects or components of a project designated under subsection (d).

I12(2) T4ApplicationsK._In order to receive a grant under the program, an applicant shall_

I13(A) submit an application to the Secretary, in such form and manner, at such time, and containing such information as the Secretary may require; and

I13(B) demonstrate to the satisfaction of the Secretary that_

I14(i) the project is financially viable;

I14(ii) the funds received will be spent efficiently and effectively; and

I14(iii) a market exists for the services of the proposed project as evidenced by contracts or written statements of intent from potential customers.

Q04

I12(3) T4Non-federal shareK._An applicant shall provide at least 20 percent of the project costs from non-Federal sources. In awarding grants under the program, the Secretary shall give a preference to those projects or components that present the most financially viable transportation services and require the lowest percentage Federal share of the costs.

