I13(A) is on other than a regular recognized or advertised route crossing the North Atlantic Ocean;

I13(B) has crossed the fishing banks of Newfoundland north of latitude 43 degrees north during the fishing season; or

I13(C) has passed through regions known or believed to be endangered by ice when proceeding to and from ports of North America.

Q04

I12(2) T4ReportingK._The name of the vessel and all pertinent information about the incident shall be reported to the government of the country to which the vessel belongs if that government requests.

Q04

