I12(1) establish procedures for testing, inspecting, and initially approving containers and designs for containers, including procedures for attaching, invalidating, and removing safety approval plates for containers;

I12(2) establish procedures to be followed by the owners of containers for the periodic examination of containers as provided in the Convention; and

I12(3) provide a method for developing, collecting, and disseminating information about container safety and the international transport of containers.

